data.COLLECTION_LOCATION: UNITED KINGDOM | Rotherham | Junction A630 A631
data.DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: complete body
data.OTHER_INFORMATION: Notes from John Rochester - "On the way to Rotherham this morning (28th June 2020) we found a dead peregrine at the side of the road, just off junction 33 of the M1 at Canklow. Looks big and weighs 940g so most probably a female. Not done any dissection yet so don't know exact date of death but possibly less than 24 hours. Injury to head and one wind consistent with being hit by a vehicle. There are some primary feathers missing from one wing. ... The dead female has a fracture through the skull and upper neck with no other significant injuries; consistent with being hit on the head by a motor vehicle. The funny looking beak is a result of the trauma. I have liver, heart and blood (separately) in 100% ethanol and in my home freezer. I also have the rest of the soft tissues in the freezer."
